cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper deals with color constancy in digital camera pipelines, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a meta-learning approach to enable fast adaptation to previously unseen cameras, which involves training a model on few-shot regression tasks. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates its approach on publicly available datasets, which indicates that it may also belong to the sub-categories of multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR).
